            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>TW: Well, for the past four or five years I have been doing multi-screen programs that use archival material with two or three projectors. This brings back a certain spectacle that you don’t get in many other ways. I will be also be doing a piece at the Strange Beauty film festival held at the Manbites Dog theater with a live band called Arrows Out. I am interested in more elaborate, more theatrical presentations of images. I would also like to do more in Durham with more local Durham films, but I just need to get more people involved.</p>
<p>One Hundred Years of Image Machines will open at Durham Cinematheque, located at 305 E. Chapel Hill Street, on Monday, December 10 and will run through May 2013.</p>

